To create a new debian package:

    0. Do
        setenv DEBEMAIL "Frank B. Brokken <f.b.brokken@rug.nl>"

    1. Keep the bisonc++/ name
    
    2. Define the next version in bisonc++/VERSION

       THEN (upgrade the version for each new distribution):

            setenv DEBEMAIL f.b.brokken@rug.nl
            cd bisonc++/debian
            dch -v [version just set in version.cc]
            cd ../..


    (See also: file:///usr/share/doc/maint-guide/
                                maint-guide.en.html/ch-update.en.html):

    3. Build a new, complete, package:
        run on a clean checkout:
            (file:///usr/share/doc/maint-guide/
                maint-guide.en.html/ch-build.en.html#s-completebuild):

        From the directory in which this file is located, do

            ./distribution
        and optionally:
            cvs commit 
            cvs tag v<version>-<revision>-<subrevision>
        
    4. Partial reruns (instead of full recompilation from scratch):
        run in bisonc++/

            fakeroot debian/rules binary

    or

        dpkg-buildpackage -rfakeroot
